waffleoRai_cafebotCommands

Class MessageQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • waffleoRai_cafebotCommands.MessageQueue

  • public class MessageQueue
extends java.lang.Object
    A deque wrapper for objects containing information about message events (ie. JDA MessageReceivedEvent). All functions accessing the internal deque are synchronized so as to reduce the potential for concurrency errors. This object is designed to be safe for access by multiple threads.
    Since:
    July 1, 2018
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Blythe Hospelhorn

    • Method Detail

      • pop

        public net.dv8tion.jda.core.events.message.MessageReceivedEvent pop()
        Pop a message event from the front of the internal deque. This method both returns the event and removes it from the deque.
        If no events are currently in the queue, this method will simply return null.
        Returns:
        The event at the front of the queue.

      • add

        Parameters:

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Get whether the queue is currently empty.
        Returns:
        True if the queue is empty. False if the queue is not empty.
